The metrics-apb is currently not compatible with the mobile-cli. Normally you would use a cli command to get the configuration for a service (like metrics):


{code}
$ mobile get clientconfig <app> --namespace=<project> -o json
{code}

For this to work some resources have to be created during the provision phase. Namely a config map and a secret (if there is secret configuration) that the mobile-cli can use to get the required config values. Those resources are missing in the metrics-apb but are implemented in the keycloak-apb which can be used as an example: https://github.com/aerogearcatalog/keycloak-apb/blob/master/roles/provision-keycloak-apb/tasks/configure-keycloak.yml#L96

